49:54.033 --> 49:57.243
Yeah, I can't talk right now
'cause I have to go to work.

49:57.411 --> 50:00.038
Oh, really?
You snaking another one of my jobs?

50:01.040 --> 50:02.540
What are you? A detective?

50:02.625 --> 50:06.836
No. But I'll search you anyway.

50:07.380 --> 50:09.005
You're cheesy.

50:09.090 --> 50:10.632
Hey, come on. You're laughing.

50:13.010 --> 50:15.261
To answer your question, no,
I'm not stealing anything.

50:15.346 --> 50:17.681
It's a job that was offered directly to me.

50:17.765 --> 50:18.973
Oh! Well, break a lung.

50:19.058 --> 50:20.308
Thanks, I won't.

50:20.393 --> 50:22.352
Bye, Carol Solomon.

50:23.062 --> 50:25.021
I'm the boss.

50:26.982 --> 50:29.984
The new Saber Tooth
bristle brush technology

50:30.069 --> 50:34.698
is patented to be soft on hair,
hard on fly-aways.

50:35.074 --> 50:39.494
Saber Tooth. Because nobody's purrr-fect.

50:43.040 --> 50:44.124
So where's Louis?

50:44.208 --> 50:46.543
- He's sick and went home early.
- He doesn't want to see you.

50:46.794 --> 50:48.503
- What?
- Not what I said.

50:48.587 --> 50:50.672
I heard through the grapevine

50:50.798 --> 50:53.425
they want you to V.O. the promo
for that crazy trilogy.

50:53.801 --> 50:55.760
And don't bust me for dropping
the broccoli.

50:55.886 --> 50:57.137
What crazy trilogy?

50:57.430 --> 50:59.764
Oh, my God, The Amazon Games!

50:59.932 --> 51:01.474
How could you not have heard of this?

51:01.559 --> 51:02.976
It's common pop knowledge.

51:03.060 --> 51:04.185
I don't have an agent.

51:04.270 --> 51:06.896
First off, it's a quadrilogy.

51:06.981 --> 51:08.022
Great.

51:08.107 --> 51:11.025
It's an adaptation of
the hyper fantasy book series.

51:11.110 --> 51:14.320
It's about these fierce mutated female
Amazonian warriors

51:14.405 --> 51:19.325
as the sole future world-inhabiting species
battling cloned prehistoric cavemen hybrids.

51:19.493 --> 51:21.077
It's all based on the Prussian War.

51:21.162 --> 51:27.041
Anyway, they're reinstating the hokey
"In a world... " gimmick

51:27.209 --> 51:28.585
and everybody's in a huff, I guess.

51:28.669 --> 51:30.920
Because it marks the rebirth of epic cinema!

51:31.005 --> 51:32.172
Whatever.

51:32.298 --> 51:35.008
I'm just glad it's a woman this time
instead of a sweaty old man.

51:35.092 --> 51:36.176
I'll see you guys.

51:36.260 --> 51:37.260
Yeah. Congrats.

51:37.344 --> 51:39.387
Thank you for dropping the broccoli.

51:40.181 --> 51:42.056
You should cut your hair.

51:42.141 --> 51:45.602
Stop trying to woo me by being mean.
It doesn't work.

51:46.437 --> 51:47.437
You want to get a drink later?

51:47.646 --> 51:48.646
Okay.

51:51.192 --> 51:53.693
Hey! Watch it!

51:54.153 --> 51:55.862
That is so rude.

51:55.946 --> 51:57.071
Excuse me. I'm so sorry.

51:57.156 --> 51:58.615
I just want to give you my card.

51:58.741 --> 52:01.159
I'm not a vocal coach anymore,
but I would make an exception for you

52:01.243 --> 52:02.702
because you sound like a squeaky toy.

52:02.870 --> 52:04.370
And I don't mean that in a bad way.

52:04.622 --> 52:07.248
I think you're better than that.
And I think we're all better than that.

52:07.333 --> 52:09.042
It's good for the species.
You know what I mean?

52:09.126 --> 52:11.544
There's also a Jamba Juice
two blocks away from here.

52:11.712 --> 52:13.379
'Cause I bet you were looking for a smoothie.

52:13.464 --> 52:15.965
Maybe not. I don't know. But if you were,

52:16.050 --> 52:17.592
you know where it is.

52:25.100 --> 52:26.851
Excited or farting?

52:31.190 --> 52:33.066
How are you?

52:34.151 --> 52:36.152
I just came back to get my cell phone.

52:36.237 --> 52:39.280
There is no way to function in
the modern world without one.

52:40.199 --> 52:42.158
Yeah. No, I know it.

52:43.911 --> 52:45.829
Do you want to talk about anything or...

52:45.913 --> 52:49.207
- There's nothing you can say, Carol.
- Right. I know. I know.

52:52.169 --> 52:54.254
I wish that there was

52:56.173 --> 52:57.590
a bubble or something, you know,

52:58.175 --> 53:00.093
that we could just step into

53:00.177 --> 53:03.555
where there was no judgment
or past or present.

53:06.225 --> 53:10.353
A bubble where I can hear her say

53:10.437 --> 53:14.190
why she did it in a vortex.

53:16.235 --> 53:21.364
Sort of. Yeah. Not the bubble part of it,
but the general...

53:21.448 --> 53:24.659
Listen, I'm staying at my friend PJ's
editing suite,

53:24.743 --> 53:26.452
- 'cause I got a lot of deadlines.
- PJ?

53:26.537 --> 53:28.162
And he's got a comfy couch

53:28.247 --> 53:29.956
and this stupid yellow lab
that definitely thinks

53:30.040 --> 53:31.249
I'm the best person that ever lived.

53:31.333 --> 53:33.668
PJ who, though? Just so I know...

53:33.794 --> 53:35.670
I really gotta be away
from everything right now. Okay?

53:35.754 --> 53:36.754
Okay.

53:39.216 --> 53:41.551
Hey. I got good news.

53:41.635 --> 53:43.052
What?

53:43.679 --> 53:47.640
Dinner at Dad's tonight.
The groupie's making casseroles.

53:48.225 --> 53:49.475
I'm ignoring that.

53:49.685 --> 53:52.478
Come on. Yum-yum.

53:52.980 --> 53:54.981
Hamburger hash.

54:00.279 --> 54:02.238
Have you spoken to Moe?

54:08.329 --> 54:12.790
I feel so lost without him.

54:15.294 --> 54:18.671
Like I can't even tell him,
you know? Because...

54:21.300 --> 54:25.011
I know. I know. If you could... If you could...

54:25.095 --> 54:30.475
If you could tell him, what would you say?

54:31.310 --> 54:36.522
In a way, that's kind of a good...
It's a good exercise

54:37.107 --> 54:41.110
to just let it out. Just let it flow.

54:41.195 --> 54:43.988
Whatever you want to say.

54:44.073 --> 54:46.032
- I am. Carol.
- Okay.

54:46.116 --> 54:47.116
Jesus.

54:48.369 --> 54:52.246
It's just that nobody takes care of me
the way that he does.

54:52.414 --> 54:54.916
I just feel really safe with him.

54:56.293 --> 54:59.879
The only thing I gave him in return
is total dishonesty.

55:00.339 --> 55:03.299
It doesn't even matter that I didn't sleep
with that asshole, right?

55:03.384 --> 55:05.802
- Tip or no tip.
- Tip, as in "gratuity"?

55:06.303 --> 55:10.264
God! I should not even have been in his
room in the first place.

55:10.349 --> 55:13.977
I hate myself. I hate myself.

55:14.353 --> 55:16.270
I hate myself for doing that.

55:16.355 --> 55:19.232
I hate myself for squandering
the most beautiful thing

55:19.316 --> 55:21.401
I ever had in my whole stupid life.

55:24.405 --> 55:30.952
I'm so scared.
I'm so scared, Carol, that I'm gonna lose him.

55:32.329 --> 55:36.708
And I'm so sad because
I'm not good enough for him

55:36.792 --> 55:38.793
and I don't deserve him.

55:39.378 --> 55:42.422
And I don't deserve his sandwich bar.

55:45.384 --> 55:49.637
Who's that hot friend of Moe's?

55:51.432 --> 55:54.434
Named PJ?

55:56.395 --> 55:58.354
'Cause I kinda want to date him.

55:58.939 --> 55:59.939
Wait, what?

56:00.024 --> 56:02.316
PJ?

56:02.401 --> 56:04.527
PJ Koopchick?

56:04.611 --> 56:08.948
PJ Koopchick. I think it was, yeah,
PJ Koopchick.

56:09.033 --> 56:10.324
He's married.

56:10.409 --> 56:15.121
Oh, my God! PJ Koopchick's married?
Jesus, another good one gone.

56:15.372 --> 56:17.373
He's really fat. Hairy.

56:17.458 --> 56:22.670
Yeah. I know. You know I like that. Like Dad.

56:22.755 --> 56:27.759
That's literally why I was always into
PJ Koopchick.

56:32.431 --> 56:33.890
What are these?

56:33.974 --> 56:35.433
Oh, they're just cherries from a can.

56:35.517 --> 56:36.559
From Canter's.

56:36.643 --> 56:38.394
No, I made it.

56:38.479 --> 56:41.731
Just kidding.
It's as Jewish as you can get in her family.

56:43.400 --> 56:44.984
That's a good one.

56:45.944 --> 56:47.403
Listen, I wanted to show you something.

56:47.988 --> 56:50.948
I came across this article I wrote
decades ago.

56:51.283 --> 56:56.287
I think it's worth a read.
Have a look at it. It's all about goals.

56:56.413 --> 56:59.082
I wish I could write.
Your father's book was so...

56:59.166 --> 57:00.166
I'll give it to you after.

57:00.250 --> 57:02.418
I'm no Philip Roth, but I try.

57:02.920 --> 57:04.087
Dani was always a really good writer.

57:04.171 --> 57:05.463
You don't have to do that.

57:05.547 --> 57:07.340
It must run in the family.

57:07.424 --> 57:10.635
My aunt Peggy writes a column
for health journal in Ohio.

57:10.761 --> 57:13.179
But she's not really related to me, 'cause
it's my mom's brother's wife.

57:15.182 --> 57:16.891
You kids with your phones.

57:16.975 --> 57:18.518
That is what I'm talking about.

57:18.769 --> 57:20.228
Oh, look at these.
They're almost too pretty to eat.

57:20.521 --> 57:23.231
So, how's the Moe situation?

57:26.485 --> 57:28.402
Listen. We're all family here.

57:28.487 --> 57:30.154
I think we can look to each other
for strength.

57:30.280 --> 57:31.447
Oh, my God!

57:31.532 --> 57:33.950
Jamie, I think, could be real helpful
in this situation.

57:34.034 --> 57:36.285
I actually have to run to the little girls' room.
Excuse me.

57:36.370 --> 57:37.495
"How's the Moe situation?"

57:37.579 --> 57:39.413
Listen, Dani. Let me tell you something.

57:39.498 --> 57:41.415
I don't think you did anything wrong.

57:41.583 --> 57:42.625
Oh, okay. Thanks, Dad.

57:42.709 --> 57:44.502
No, I mean it. Moe's gonna get over this.

57:44.628 --> 57:46.254
Okay. I'm sure.

57:46.505 --> 57:48.881
You know, people make mistakes in life.
I know I have.

57:49.675 --> 57:53.427
Marriage is all about forgiveness.
Your mother understood that.

57:53.512 --> 57:55.263
Yeah! Mom totally understood that.

57:55.389 --> 57:56.430
She understood it completely.

57:56.515 --> 57:59.433
I mean, she did OD on the prescription
meds that she had to take

57:59.518 --> 58:01.435
to deal with the anxiety that you caused her.

58:01.520 --> 58:03.146
In the first place, let me explain something.

58:03.230 --> 58:04.397
I don't want to split hairs, Dad.

58:04.481 --> 58:06.440
Your mother had a deep affection
for Sudafed,

58:06.525 --> 58:09.152
which accidentally interfered
with her love affair with Valium.

58:09.236 --> 58:10.444
It was Xanax. It was definitely Xanax.

58:10.529 --> 58:11.571
Don't start!

58:11.655 --> 58:14.115
She was going out with Howard Wetson
when she died!

58:14.199 --> 58:16.659
At least Howard Wetson
knows I don't like bell peppers!

58:16.743 --> 58:19.871
For Christ's sake, it was 16 years ago.
Would you let it pass?

58:19.955 --> 58:23.791
Jesus Christ. The moment I find one little
iota of happiness

58:23.876 --> 58:26.460
the two of you have to start blaming
your mother's death on me.

58:26.545 --> 58:29.505
- No one's blaming you, okay?
- Don't be so crass.

58:29.590 --> 58:31.424
You're blaming yourself!

58:31.508 --> 58:34.969
So Mom died. Do we need to rehash that?

58:35.137 --> 58:36.762
I feel like we really got into...

58:36.847 --> 58:38.181
Here, Jamie, try some of these.
They're very good.

58:38.265 --> 58:39.557
I don't want to eat them all myself.

58:39.641 --> 58:42.643
I already had one, but, yeah,
they're pretty good.

58:43.020 --> 58:44.103
So, I have news.

58:44.188 --> 58:46.814
What news? You're not pregnant, are you?

58:46.982 --> 58:48.357
All we need.

58:48.442 --> 58:49.483
Oh, I'm just kidding.

58:49.568 --> 58:51.485
No, I've been working.

58:51.612 --> 58:53.905
- The vocal coaching, right?
- Terrific, yeah.

58:54.031 --> 58:58.326
No, no. I just booked these two voice over...
Like, movie trailer voice over gigs.

58:58.535 --> 59:01.454
And I wanted to share that with you
because it all started

59:01.538 --> 59:04.373
because I swiped this really big job
from Gustav Warner,

59:04.583 --> 59:07.251
who I finally met at the party you guys
brought me to.

59:07.419 --> 59:11.839
And now I'm going to be the voice
of this new epic quadrilogy.

59:11.965 --> 59:15.176
And I get to be the first woman to utter
the words "In a world... "

59:15.469 --> 59:16.677
Sam!

59:17.137 --> 59:19.263
- Are you okay?
- Dad, have some water.

59:19.681 --> 59:23.434
Excuse me. Wait a second.
That's you? You're the thief?

59:23.644 --> 59:25.519
The what?

59:25.604 --> 59:27.521
"The thief," it sounds like a crime novel.

59:27.606 --> 59:29.106
You're dating Gustav Warner?

59:29.191 --> 59:30.608
Wait. How do you know about that?

59:30.692 --> 59:32.568
It's more like fucking probably
than I would say dating.

59:32.653 --> 59:35.404
Jesus Christ!
Why don't you tell me any of this stuff?

59:35.656 --> 59:37.365
You don't ask about the stuff.

59:37.449 --> 59:39.075
You don't ever ask about us or anything.

59:39.159 --> 59:41.953
Sam, a daughter should not have to share
her sex life with her father.

59:42.037 --> 59:43.663
Yes, thank you, Jamie. I appreciate it.

59:43.872 --> 59:48.376
Listen, sweetheart, let me explain something
to you, okay? This is a business.

59:48.585 --> 59:51.796
An industry you've seen from
arm's length for your entire life.

59:51.880 --> 59:52.922
And there's a reason for that.

59:53.006 --> 59:57.134
You don't just put one promo,
one trailer on your rsum

59:57.219 --> 59:59.262
and expect to get
a gigantic job like that.

59:59.388 --> 01:00:02.848
I've booked, actually, three movie trailer
gigs and then now this quadrilogy.

01:00:03.100 --> 01:00:04.767
You have to understand
something, sweetheart.

01:00:04.851 --> 01:00:06.686
They would never try and resurrect

01:00:06.770 --> 01:00:11.107
something this important,
this iconic with a freshman vocal.

01:00:11.692 --> 01:00:14.610
It's not done.

01:00:16.613 --> 01:00:19.615
Well, I think I could go for some
of that nice green tea.

01:00:19.700 --> 01:00:21.033
Could we have some of that?

01:00:21.243 --> 01:00:23.160
I don't drink caffeine, remember?

01:00:23.328 --> 01:00:26.706
Yes. Clearly, I forgot about that, Jamie.

01:00:27.582 --> 01:00:28.666
Carol?

01:00:28.750 --> 01:00:30.584
- Can we go, please?
- Carol! Don't. Wait.

01:00:30.669 --> 01:00:31.961
- Do you want me to start it?
- Carol! Wait.

01:00:32.045 --> 01:00:33.129
- Do I have the keys?
- Carol, would you wait?

01:00:33.213 --> 01:00:35.172
I'm in my heels. I've been working all day.

01:00:35.257 --> 01:00:36.590
- I can't even walk.
- I'm sorry.

01:00:36.675 --> 01:00:40.136
I don't believe him.
I think he's lying about the whole quadrilogy.

01:00:40.220 --> 01:00:42.722
It's fine. He's a legend.
It makes sense they would give him the line.

01:00:42.806 --> 01:00:43.848
I call bullshit. I call bullshit.

01:00:43.932 --> 01:00:47.601
Because that man cannot let anybody
in this whole goddamn family shine

01:00:47.686 --> 01:00:49.979
because Nana was a cunt to him
when he was a little kid.

01:00:50.063 --> 01:00:51.731
Nana was a survivor.
You should be easy on Nana.

01:00:51.815 --> 01:00:53.607
Yeah, right. You know what?
You gotta believe me.

01:00:53.692 --> 01:00:56.610
You cannot expect that man
to ever be supportive of you.

01:00:56.737 --> 01:00:58.612
He is totally incapable of that.

01:00:58.697 --> 01:01:01.115
I think the studio is going to be very
pleased to learn

01:01:01.199 --> 01:01:03.951
that I've been reconsidering
and now I'm very much interested

01:01:04.036 --> 01:01:05.494
in doing the quadrilogy gig.

01:01:05.579 --> 01:01:06.829
For what? The Amazon Games?

01:01:06.913 --> 01:01:07.997
Exactly.

01:01:08.081 --> 01:01:09.123
Sam, it's too late.

01:01:09.207 --> 01:01:10.249
What do you mean, "Too late"?

01:01:10.417 --> 01:01:11.751
How am I supposed to tell them to recast it?

01:01:11.835 --> 01:01:14.587
Because I'm Sam goddamn Sotto.
That's why.

01:01:14.671 --> 01:01:15.838
The studio wants Carol.

01:01:15.922 --> 01:01:20.426
I suppose you can put yourself on tape.
Give it a shot.

01:01:20.594 --> 01:01:22.136
Very well then. So be it. Okay.

01:01:22.429 --> 01:01:26.307
In that case, I will put myself on tape
with everybody else.

01:01:26.767 --> 01:01:28.726
And I will conquer.

01:01:29.269 --> 01:01:32.646
Alla! Before you leave make me one more
of those soy white Russians.

01:01:32.731 --> 01:01:33.898
I'm sorry, Siegel. What were you saying?

01:01:33.982 --> 01:01:36.484
You're not gonna believe this,
but Sotto, he's back in.

01:01:36.568 --> 01:01:37.651
To what? Amazon Games?

01:01:37.736 --> 01:01:39.653
Your girlfriend's not the only one
to beat out now.

01:01:39.738 --> 01:01:41.697
The legend himself? Are you kidding me?

01:01:41.782 --> 01:01:43.657
I thought you guys were pals?

01:01:43.742 --> 01:01:44.784
Yeah, so did I.

01:01:44.951 --> 01:01:48.788
You're not gonna be able to screw yourself
out of a voice over battle with Sotto.

01:01:57.756 --> 01:01:59.757
"Better than a bubble. "

01:02:02.761 --> 01:02:04.845
How am I gonna play this?

01:02:17.734 --> 01:02:18.943
Hey.

01:02:19.736 --> 01:02:21.529
Your voice sounds bad. Are you sick?

01:02:21.738 --> 01:02:25.616
Oh, no. I just woke up

01:02:25.742 --> 01:02:28.244
'cause I was up talking to my sister till late.

01:02:28.662 --> 01:02:31.664
Right, where are you now?

01:02:31.790 --> 01:02:34.708
I'm at my sister's place in Koreatown.

01:02:34.793 --> 01:02:36.085
Yeah, Koreatown. That's funny

01:02:36.169 --> 01:02:40.506
because I'm right in your neighborhood.
I'm pretty much right near you right now.

01:02:40.757 --> 01:02:42.758
Hey! Why don't we get a snack?

01:02:42.843 --> 01:02:44.677
Let's get a snack.

01:02:44.761 --> 01:02:45.761
All right.

01:02:45.846 --> 01:02:51.392
But I'm gonna need a second to spiff up.

01:02:51.560 --> 01:02:53.686
Totally. You know what?
You take a couple of minutes.

01:02:53.812 --> 01:02:56.730
You know, I'll just text you where I am
and just meet me downstairs

01:02:56.815 --> 01:02:58.357
and then we'll figure it out.

01:03:02.779 --> 01:03:03.904
I'm sorry.

01:03:03.989 --> 01:03:05.489
I'm good. That's cool.

01:03:05.824 --> 01:03:08.200
I got you a hot water with lemon.

01:03:09.077 --> 01:03:10.453
Gargle that.

01:03:10.537 --> 01:03:12.746
Oh, I'm good on the gargle.

01:03:12.831 --> 01:03:13.914
- Sure. Whatever.
- Thank you.

01:03:13.999 --> 01:03:15.708
You want to take a walk?

01:03:15.792 --> 01:03:16.917
Sure.

01:03:21.798 --> 01:03:25.759
Okay, here's the deal. My life consists
mainly of work, family, fantasy baseball.

01:03:25.844 --> 01:03:27.720
You do that? I didn't know you did that.

01:03:27.804 --> 01:03:29.597
- Yeah, Rotisserie League with my friends.
- Oh, right on.

01:03:30.849 --> 01:03:33.267
I'm not a meddler, okay? But I like you.

01:03:33.351 --> 01:03:34.727
So when I heard something about you...

01:03:34.811 --> 01:03:36.145
What did you hear about me?

01:03:36.396 --> 01:03:37.771
I'm not done with my speech here.

01:03:37.856 --> 01:03:39.523
Oh, I didn't know there was a speech.

01:03:39.608 --> 01:03:41.317
Yes, it's a pitch. To be precise.

01:03:41.401 --> 01:03:42.485
Is that a baseball reference?

01:03:42.569 --> 01:03:43.777
No, no. It's a literal pitch,

01:03:43.862 --> 01:03:46.113
like I want to pitch you an idea
kind of thing, okay?

01:03:46.198 --> 01:03:47.948
So, I grew up with three sisters.

01:03:48.033 --> 01:03:49.825
So I've always been into women's rights.

01:03:49.910 --> 01:03:52.495
And I listen to the Cranberries openly.

01:03:52.579 --> 01:03:54.079
Oh, what about Zombie or Linger?

01:03:54.831 --> 01:03:56.040
Linger. I like Linger better.

01:03:56.124 --> 01:03:57.958
